1 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
2 (2) “Indirect costs” means any costs that would be considered to be indirect
3 costs under OMB Uniform Guidance.
4 (3) “Nonprofit organization” means an organization that is tax exempt
5 under § 501(c)(3), (4), or (6) of the Internal Revenue Code.
6 (4) “OMB Uniform Guidance” means the Uniform Administrative
7 Requirements, Cost Principles, and Audit Requirements for Federal Awards adopted by the
8 Office of Management and Budget in 2 C.F.R. 200 and any related guidance published by
9 the Office of Management and Budget.
10 (b) (1) This section applies only to:
11 (i) a grant or contract awarded on or after October 1, 2018;
12 (ii) a multi–year grant or contract awarded before October 1, 2018,
13 if:
14 1. the grant or contract continues to be in effect on or after
15 October 1, 2018; and
16 2. funding for the grant or contract is required to be
17 authorized separately for each fiscal year; and
18 (iii) an extension or a renewal of a grant or contract if the extension
19 or renewal is awarded on or after July 1, 2019.
20 (2) This section applies whether or not the funds awarded through the
21 grant or contract are transferred directly by the State or through a third party to the
22 nonprofit organization.
23 (3) This section does not require the reimbursement of indirect costs
24 incurred under a multi–year grant or contract described under paragraph (1)(ii) of this
25 subsection during any fiscal year that begins before July 1, 2019.
26 (c) If a nonprofit organization is a direct recipient or subrecipient of a grant or
27 contract for the provision of services that is funded wholly with State funds or with a
28 combination of State and other nonfederal funds, the terms of the grant or contract shall
29 allow for reimbursement of indirect costs:
30 (1) at the same rate the nonprofit organization has negotiated and
31 received:
32 (i) for indirect costs under a direct federal award; or

